# Targeted Verification (Concurrent-Agent Safe)

When multiple agents run concurrently, running `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint` workspace-wide causes lock contention, duplicate Turborepo cache misses, and 30–90s delays. **Run targeted checks on touched paths instead.**

## Post-task gate (default — use this)

```powershell
# 1. ESLint: only the files/directories you touched (~5s)
pnpm exec eslint --max-warnings=0 <path1> [path2 ...]

# 2. TypeScript: incremental full graph (~10s warm, skips unchanged)
pnpm typecheck
```

### Choosing your ESLint target path

| What you touched | Path to pass |
|---|---|
| One file | `app/[locale]/o/[orgSlug]/apps/contacts/page.tsx` |
| A feature module | `lib/features/contacts/` |
| Shell components | `components2/app-shell/` |
| Multiple dirs | `lib/features/hrm/ components2/app-shell/` |
| Whole area | `app/ lib/` (only when you touched >10 files spread across both) |

**Never pass `./` or omit a path** — that triggers the full workspace ESLint scan.

## When to run full workspace commands

| Scenario | Command |
|---|---|
| You are the **only** agent running | `pnpm typecheck && pnpm lint` |
| Pre-push / opening a PR | `pnpm verify:parallel` |
| Drizzle schema change | `pnpm lint:drizzle-journal` (narrow) |
| i18n message catalog change | `pnpm lint:fixtures-parity` (narrow) |
| Design token change (`globals.css`) | `pnpm lint` (design-contract must re-run) |

## TypeScript note

`pnpm typecheck` (`tsc --noEmit`) always resolves the full project graph — true per-file TS checking is not supported. However, the `.tsbuildinfo` cache makes it **~10s warm** vs 60s cold. Two agents running `pnpm typecheck` simultaneously on different files is safe (read-only); contention only arises from the `.tsbuildinfo` write at the end. Accept this or stagger by 5s if you hit write conflicts.

## Close condition (concurrent context)

```txt
Task is closed only when:
  pnpm exec eslint --max-warnings=0 <touched-paths> → exits 0
  pnpm typecheck → exits 0
  No import targets a file that does not exist on disk
  No redirect targets a deleted route
```
